><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
The 'deductive reasoning' (<i>rationibus probatum</i>) seems to be the 
arguments alleged in Chap. <A HREF="gc3_25.htm">XXV</a>. What St Thomas 
here calls 'induction' is the noted <i>inductio per enumerationem 
simplicem</i>. He has enumerated all other alternatives and shown that 
this alone remains tenable. We might call it the 'method of residues.' 

